main event: Radar detection of an unidentified object by the FAA Control Center in Norfolk, Virginia.
interesting points: The object was tracked on radar from 1530 to 1550, maintaining an altitude of approximately 2,000 feet, a speed of approximately 200 knots, and a southeasterly course.
No known aircraft were in the area at the time, and the object did not give any positive responses to radar interrogation.
The object was beyond visual range, and no further details were obtained.
An investigation was conducted, but no physical evidence or traces were found at the reported sighting locations.
The investigations were inconclusive regarding the nature and origin of the reported sightings.
